    <section>
        <title>wrapper.console.loglevel</title>
        <para>
            Log level to use for console output.  Valid log levels include:
            <literal moreinfo="none">NONE</literal> for no output,
            <literal moreinfo="none">FATAL</literal> to only show fatal
            error messages, <literal moreinfo="none">ERROR</literal> to
            show all error messages, <literal moreinfo="none">STATUS</literal>
            to show all state changes, <literal moreinfo="none">INFO</literal>
            shows all JVM output and informative messages, and
            <literal moreinfo="none">DEBUG</literal> shows detailed debug
            information.  The default value is
            <literal moreinfo="none">INFO</literal>.
        </para>
        <informalexample>
            <simpara><emphasis>Example:</emphasis></simpara>
            <screen format="linespecific"><![CDATA[wrapper.console.loglevel=INFO]]></screen>
        </informalexample>
    </section>
</chapter>
